mouth of the Duckabush River in Washington | map1_locator = Washington <!-- *** Websites *** --> | commons = }} The '''Duckabush River''' is located in the [[Olympic Peninsula]] in [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]], [[USA]]. It rises near [[Mount Duckabush]] in the [[Olympic Mountains]] within the [[Olympic National Park]] and drains to [[Hood Canal]], an arm of [[Puget Sound]]. The name Duckabush comes from the Indian word ''do-hi-a-boos'', meaning "reddish face", referring to the reddish bluffs in the area.<ref>{{cite book |last= Phillips |first= James W. |title= Washington State Place Names |year= 1971 |publisher= University of Washington Press |isbn= 0-295-95158-3}}</ref> ==See also== *[[List of Washington rivers]] ==References== {{reflist|colwidth=30em}} ==External links== *[http://www.nps.gov/olym/ National Park Service - Olympic National Park] [[Category:Rivers of Washington (state)]] [[Category:Landforms of Jefferson County, Washington]] {{washington-geo-stub}}
